Since you're logging in using a Service Principal, the error is almost certainly due to the service principal not having permission to read secrets from the Key Vault.

The error confirms this:

ForbiddenByRbac
Assignment: (not found)

Caller:
appid=48526d55-b2fc-4a55-96ff-22845f827cb8
oid=b82020e2-c06c-483c-ace6-2f69ac79b162

This means Terraform authenticated successfully, but Azure RBAC cannot find any role assignment that allows this service principal to read secrets.

Step 1: Verify the Service Principal
az login --service-principal \
  --username <CLIENT_ID> \
  --password <CLIENT_SECRET> \
  --tenant <TENANT_ID>

Verify:

az account show
Step 2: Assign Key Vault Secrets User Role

Get the Key Vault Resource ID:

KV_ID=$(az keyvault show \
  --name gopal-win-vault \
  --resource-group gopal-vault \
  --query id -o tsv)

Assign the role:

az role assignment create \
  --assignee 48526d55-b2fc-4a55-96ff-22845f827cb8 \
  --role "Key Vault Secrets User" \
  --scope $KV_ID

Or using the object ID:

az role assignment create \
  --assignee-object-id b82020e2-c06c-483c-ace6-2f69ac79b162 \
  --role "Key Vault Secrets User" \
  --scope $KV_ID
Step 3: Verify
az role assignment list \
    --assignee 48526d55-b2fc-4a55-96ff-22845f827cb8 \
    --scope $KV_ID \
    --output table

Expected:

Role
------------------------
Key Vault Secrets User
Step 4: Wait

RBAC takes a few minutes to propagate.

Wait 5–10 minutes.
